        <p>Open Source Chandigarh is a dynamic and vibrant tech community, powered by Chitkara University. It aims to create a rich demographic of open-source practitioners in the Tricity (Chandigarh, Panchkula, and Mohali).</p>
        
        <p>Open Source Chandigarh has a number of community partners, including:</p>
        
        <ul>
            <li>Apache Local Community Indore</li>
            <li>Docker Inc.</li>
            <li>GitHub</li>
            <li>Collabnix</li>
            <li>OpsTree Solutions</li>
            <li>Webiny</li>
        </ul>
        
        <p>These partners provide support in a variety of ways, such as:</p>
        
        <ul>
            <li>Conducting workshops and events</li>
            <li>Providing mentorship and guidance</li>
            <li>Sponsoring projects</li>
            <li>Helping to connect members with job opportunities</li>
        </ul>
        
        <p>Open Source Chandigarh is a great resource for anyone interested in learning about or contributing to open source software. It provides a platform for members to connect with each other, collaborate on projects, and share their knowledge.</p>
        
        <p>Here are some of the benefits of being a part of the Open Source Chandigarh community:</p>
        
        <ul>
            <li>Access to workshops and events on a variety of open source topics</li>
            <li>Mentorship and guidance from experienced developers</li>
            <li>Opportunities to collaborate on projects with other members</li>
            <li>Access to job opportunities from community partners</li>
            <li>A supportive and welcoming community of open source enthusiasts</li>
        </ul>
